ol.li:
r^2 = 24^2 + 10^2 = 676, so r = \sqrt{676} = 26. Then 
        \cos (\theta) = \dfrac{x}{r} = \dfrac{24}{26} =\dfrac{12}{13}
            \sin(\theta) = \dfrac{y}{r} = \dfrac{10}{26} =\dfrac{5}{13}
            \tan(\theta) = \dfrac{y}{x} = \dfrac{10}{24} =\dfrac{5}{12}

